    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "it doesn't feel like \"settling into a rhythm\" though. it feels more like the map is just... blank. like i've reached the edge of the world and there isn't any more terrain to cover. everyone talks about the journey being the point, but what if you've just seen enough? what if the trip is simply over?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It's completely valid to reach a point where the initial excitement of discovery fades. Feeling like the map is blank suggests you're ready for a different kind of adventure—one that doesn't require a destination. Consider what you actually *want* next, rather than what a \"good trip\" should entail. Maybe the next leg isn't a new country, but a new kind of engagement with the world around you.",
      "source": "target",
