    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i don't think i want a new engagement with the world. i keep thinking about how some travelers just... decide to end their journey. not because they're lost, but because they're done. they've seen the sights, they've finished the tour, and they just want to step off the path and find some peace. it feels more like a completion than a failure. does that make sense? like, just closing the book because the story is finished?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
